nal\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Types-of-Apprenticeships.aspx/\" title=\"Types of apprenticeships\">Apprenticeships</a> website.</p>\n\n<h2>Apply</h2>\n\n<p>Get started and <a href=\"/apply-apprenticeship\" title=\"Apply for an apprenticeship\">apply for an apprenticeship</a>.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/apprenticeships-guide/taking-on-an-apprentice","slug":"taking-on-an-apprentice","order":3,"title":"Taking on an apprentice","body":"<p>You can use apprenticeships to train both new and existing employees. You can get funding to train apprentices.</p>\n\n<h2>Funding</h2>\n\n<p>The amount of funding you can get for apprenticeship training depends on your sector and the age of your candidate:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>aged 16 to 18 - you get 100% of cost paid</li>\n  <li>aged 19 to 24 - you get 50% of cost paid</li>\n  <li>25 years and older - you may only get a contribution</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This is paid directly to the organisation that provides and supports the apprenticeship - in most cases the learning provider.</p>\n\n<h2>Apprenticeship grant for employers</h2>\n\n<p>You may also be eligible for a £1,500 <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Employers/Steps-to-make-it-happen/Incentive.aspx\" title=\"Employer incentive grants\">apprenticeship grant.</a> </p>\n\n<p>These grants are available to help small-medium sized employers to recruit up to 3 apprentices for the first time, and are in addition to the training costs you get for apprentices.</p>\n\n<h2>Take on an apprentice</h2>\n\n<p>Follow the steps on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Employers/Steps-to-make-it-happen.aspx\" title=\"Steps to make it happen\">Apprenticeships</a> website to get started.</p>\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-25T23:02:02+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Finding a job","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ffinding-job.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes job search, volunteering, apprenticeships and