 Communication Technology\">ICT</abbr></li>\n  <li>English for Speakers of Other Languages (<abbr title=\"English for Speakers of Other Languages\">ESOL</abbr>) </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Qualification levels</h3>\n\n<p>Qualifications are available at the following levels:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>entry level (<abbr title=\"Information Communication Technology\">ICT</abbr> is only available at this level)</li>\n  <li>level 1</li>\n  <li>level 2</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Qualifications in <abbr title=\"Information Communication Technology\">ICT</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>The European Computer Driving Licence (<abbr title=\"European Computer Driving Licence\">ECDL</abbr>) is a qualification from the British Computer Society which is recognised internationally. You can do it in a learning centre or as a flexible distance learning course. </p>\n\n<p>The Computer Literacy and Information Technology (<abbr title=\"Computer Literacy and Information Technology\">CLAIT</abbr>) course is a nationally-recognised qualification. You can study it at 3 levels - new, plus and advanced. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can find out more about the <a href=\"https://nationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk/advice/courses/typesoflearning/Pages/computerskills.aspx\" title=\"ECDL and CLAIT qualifications\" rel=\"external\"><abbr title=\"European Computer Driving Licence\">ECDL</abbr> and <abbr title=\"Computer Literacy and Information Technology\">CLAIT</abbr> qualifications</a> on the National Careers Service website.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Find a course</h2>\n\n<p>You can look for courses near you using the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://nationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk/advice/courses/Pages/default.aspx/\" title=\"National Careers Service course search\">National Careers Service course search</a> or by calling the helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>National Careers Service helpline</strong><br />\n0800 100 900 <br />\n8am to 10pm, 7 days a week</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Hel